SO much has happened in celebville romance this month, with some couples announcing their break-ups and others announcing pregnancies. As February is known as the month of love, some couples are still going strong. This includes actress Dawn Thandeka King and her bae Mlungisi Duncan, who have been seen head over heels in love. It is not clear when the couple started dating, but the public started noticing when they wore yellow matching outfits at Baby Cele and Thabo Maloka’s wedding in October 2019. Dawn confirmed the romance when Daily Sun asked her during the same year. It looks like the love birds gained their freedom and stopped hiding the affair from the public after their relationship made headlines. Since then, they have been spotted in different shows in matching outfits, and it seems like they can’t keep away from each other. Dawn shared that they respected each other. “Every relationship has its hiccups, but love keeps us going strong. We respect and celebrate each other,” she said. Mlungisi is an actor who shot to fame when he played loan shark Nongoloza on Uzalo. And, the two has been working together in different projects.